cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the design principles and challenges of building conversational agents for health, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC), natural language processing (cs.CL), cybernetics (cs.CY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC, followed by cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.AI, and cs.SI.
